## Implementation Plan

### Design: Two hook types

```ts
type HookEvent = "tool_result" | "before_tool_call";

interface HookState {
  store: ProjectFile;
  toolName: string;
  toolInput?: any;
  toolContent?: any[];  // existing content for tool_result
  extra?: Record<string, any>;
}

// Side-effect hooks: run in order, no return value
interface SideEffectHook {
  id: string;
  label: string;
  event: HookEvent;
  kind: "side-effect";
  condition: (state: HookState) => boolean;
  handler: (state: HookState, helpers: HookHelpers) => void;
  priority: number;
  modes?: string[];
}

// Result modifier hooks: can augment tool result content
interface ResultModifierHook {
  id: string;
  label: string;
  event: HookEvent;
  kind: "result-modifier";
  condition: (state: HookState) => boolean;
  handler: (state: HookState) => { text: string } | undefined;
  priority: number;
  modes?: string[];
}

type Hook = SideEffectHook | ResultModifierHook;

// Helpers passed to side-effect hooks (sendMessage, save, etc.)
interface HookHelpers {
  sendMessage: (msg: any, opts?: any) => void;
  save: (store: ProjectFile) => void;
  refreshStatus: (ctx: any) => void;
}
```

### Hooks to register:

| ID | Kind | Event | Current Location |
|----|------|-------|-----------------|
| `refresh-status` | side-effect | tool_result | index.ts:73-75 |
| `write-gate` | result-modifier | tool_result | index.ts:78-97 (orchestration) |
| `auto-capture-files` | side-effect | tool_result | index.ts:100-122 |
| `policy-trigger` | side-effect | tool_result | index.ts:125-141 (orchestration) |

### Dispatcher flow:
1. On `tool_result`: build HookState from event
2. Run all matching side-effect hooks (in priority order)
3. Run all matching result-modifier hooks — first non-empty result wins (or merge)
4. Return modified result (or undefined)

### Relationship with Context Engine:
- Write-gate and policy-trigger hooks still call `compose()` internally — they're *orchestration* hooks that bridge the Hook Registry to the Context Engine
- The Hook Registry doesn't replace context rules, it replaces the *inline wiring* in index.ts

### Result: index.ts tool_result handler becomes ~5 lines:
```ts
pi.on("tool_result", async (event, ctx) => {
  return dispatch("tool_result", { store: load(), toolName: event.toolName, toolInput: event.input, toolContent: event.content }, helpers);
});
```
